name: Mud House (Cafe)
directions: Ask counter staff to use the restroom, it is through the kitchen.
comment:
I hadn’t yet ordered when I asked to use it (but indicated I was planning on it), don’t know whether non-customers would be allowed.
Additionally you do have to ask, for context I’m non-binary, have had chest surgery and stubble from T (generally assumed to be a cis man) and was wearing my hair in adorable multi-color side buns, eyeliner and awesome vibrant red lipstick. I had no trouble with the folks staffing it today, but can’t say how it would be other times.

comment: Ask for a code at any restaurants in the Cargo units.

name: Northgate Mall
directions: In the food court, you'll find a hallway. At the end are the men's and women's room. Take a right and you'll find the family lounge.
comment:
There are multiple single stall bathrooms and an area for changing children and a love seat to relax.
The gendered restrooms do not have changing tables.

name: Best Buy
directions:
In the back. 
When you enter, if you head right, directly towards customer service, take a left and walk past the computers. You'll come up on the TV section. Stay to the right side of the store. There is a short hallway to the right and the restrooms are directly down it.
comment:
My wife works here and it is a very safe space. Even when I don't feel comfortable using the correct restroom other places, I have no problem going here just for the bathroom.
A large portion of the staff is part of the LGBTQ+ community, and a few (my wife included) are trans/NB.
